name: Baked Salmon Wontons
author: SaHm09
summary: It is a wonton filled with cream cheese, jalapeno, onion, salmon, and chili powder. My husband thought it sounded weird, but then ate one and loved them!
ingredients: 1 tablespoon olive oil, or as needed
directions: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Spray a baking dish lightly with cooking spray
Mix cream cheese, salmon, onion, jalapenos, and chili powder together in a medium bowl
Place a teaspoon of the salmon mixture into each wonton wrapper
Dab the edges with water, fold in corners, and pinch together
Brush tops and sides of wontons with olive oil and place into the prepared baking dish
Bake in the preheated oven until tops are golden brown, about 10 minutes
